---
// GET /llms.txt — Machine-readable documentation for AI agents
export const prerender = false;

const body = `# My MCP Shelf — LLM Discovery Endpoints

> https://www.mymcpshelf.com/llms.txt

My MCP Shelf is a curated, security-graded directory of Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers.
Every listed server carries a composite trust score, reliability tier, green-hosting badge,
and security scan result. Use these endpoints to query the directory programmatically.

## Public JSON Endpoints

All endpoints accept GET requests, require no authentication, and return JSON with CORS headers.

### 1. Search (plain English)
GET https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/search-ai?q={query}&limit={limit}
- Natural-language search across the curated directory.
- Response includes: id, name, description, category, stars, composite_trust, reliability, green_score, scan_badge, security_audit.
- Example: curl "https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/search-ai?q=postgres+safe+read&limit=5"

### 2. List servers (paginated)
GET https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/servers?q={query}&category={category}&limit={limit}&offset={offset}
- Paginated server list with full badge data.
- Response includes: servers[], total, offset, limit, has_more.
- Each server includes: composite_trust, reliability, green_score, scan_badge, install_count, installs_24h, installs_7d.

### 3. Server detail
GET https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/servers/{id}
- Full server details including security audit, reliability breakdown, env schema, CLI command/args.
- Response includes: composite_trust, green_score, scan, reliability, security, verified.

### 4. Security scan status
GET https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/security/scan-status?server_id={id}
GET https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/security/scan-status?ids={id1},{id2},... (batch, max 100)
- Returns badge_tier, scan_summary, individual scan results, and CVE matches.

### 5. Featured servers
GET https://www.mymcpshelf.com/api/v1/featured
- Curated featured servers for homepage display.

## MCP Server (installable)
Install the directory as an MCP server so agents can query it directly:
  npx -y mymcpshelf-mcp

Tools exposed:
  - search_mcp_servers(query, limit?) — ranked results with trust badges
  - get_server(id) — full details + security grade
  - get_server_security_grade(id) — composite trust, reliability, green score

The MCP server queries the live API by default and falls back to bundled static data when offline.

## Authentication
None required. All public endpoints are open.

## Rate Limits
- Search endpoints: 60 requests per minute per IP.
- Detail endpoints: 300 requests per minute per IP.

## Key Differentiators in Every Response
- composite_trust: unified score from automated security, activity, and documentation checks.
- reliability: score based on stars trajectory, issue response time, fork activity, download trends, and commit frequency.
- green_score: hosting sustainability badge (green_verified / user_dependent / unknown).
- scan_badge: security scan tier (scanned / manually_reviewed / unverified) with overall score.
`;

export async function GET() {
  return new Response(body, {
    status: 200,
    headers: {
      'Content-Type': 'text/plain; charset=utf-8',
      'Cache-Control': 'public, max-age=3600',
    },
  });
}
